verbs.description: relocate (third-person singular simple present relocates, present participle relocating, simple past and past participle relocated)

entries.meaning: (transitive) to move (something) from one place to another.
examples: We had to relocate the magazine rack because we bruised our shins on it too frequently when it was near the door.

entries.meaning: (intransitive) to change one's domicile or place of business.
examples: Alfred relocated to Colorado Springs to take advantage of the boom in the defense industry.
